  "commentary": "With SPX at 6602.5 sitting just below the flip at 6614 and between major GEX walls at 6590 (-41B) and 6610 (+72B), dealers are currently in accumulation mode, buying dips as they're long gamma in this PIN regime. The massive positive gamma wall at 6610 (+72B) will create significant selling pressure if we rally there, while the negative gamma at 6590 creates a volatility amplification zone that dealers will defend by buying aggressively. The recent GEX surge with -35.6% 1-min change suggests dealers just added significant hedging positions, reinforcing the 6590-6610 range boundaries.\n\nKey levels: Watch for dealer selling into 6610 strength and aggressive buying if we test 6590 support.\n\nBottom line: expect price to ping-pong between 6590 and 6610 with limited breakout potential.",
